  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisite</strong>: Temporal Stopwatch, 17th level</p><hr /><p>As an action, you can select a space you can see within 90 feet. All creatures within a 5-foot radius sphere centering on the selected space must succeed a Wisdom saving throw. A creature can willingly fail this saving throw. On a failed save, you can make them perform one of the following;</p><ul><li><p>Reverse: On the affected creatures next turn, they repeat the last set of actions they completed, regardless of what it was, even targeting the same space, even if no creatures are occupying it.</p></li><li><p>Pause: Creatures are stunned until the end of their next turn.</p></li><li><p>Fast Forward: Creatures immediately perform their turn as if it was their turn in the initiative order.</p></li></ul><p>You can use this Malleable Mirage once per long rest.</p>",
